records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody.
The State moves to delete the enhancer of "2nd and subsequent offense" on count 1.  Motion granted.
NO CONTEST plea entered to the amended charge of PTC deliver Morphine in count 1.  Convicted.
The State moves to dismiss and read in count 2.  Motion granted.
The defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of six (6) years.  That is two (2) years initial confinement followed by four (4) years extended supervision, concurrent with the sentence on 05 CF 361.
Defendant is found eligible for the Substance Abuse Program but not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1) pay $250.00 buy money to Metro Drug Unit, joint and several with Tristan Jimenez;
2) maintain absolute sobriety;
3) AODA assessment and follow through;
4) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
5) defendant is to use one doctor to prescribe medication and use only one pharmacy;
6) Provide a DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
7) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
8) pay court costs.
Defendant has credit for 24 days.
Minutes.
